            "title": "Consumismo na inf\u00e2ncia : um olhar sobre a escola, professores e crian\u00e7as da educa\u00e7\u00e3o infantil",
            "abstract": [
                "A sociedade de consumo destr\u00f3i a sa\u00fade planet\u00e1ria, pois al\u00e9m de degradar cada vez mais o meio ambiente como se houvesse uma fonte inesgot\u00e1vel de recursos naturais, contribui negativamente para a forma\u00e7\u00e3o de cidad\u00e3os inconscientes de suas necessidades reais e j\u00e1 afeta a forma\u00e7\u00e3o da identidade de crian\u00e7as desde a primeira inf\u00e2ncia, pois elas s\u00e3o provocadas ao ter objetos e a consumir artefatos culturais sem nenhuma criticidade, em sobreposi\u00e7\u00e3o ao ser. O consumismo infantil acarreta v\u00e1rios problemas na inf\u00e2ncia (ansiedade, stress familiar, necessidades criadas e desejos reprimidos, obesidade, erotiza\u00e7\u00e3o precoce, etc). Considerando que a forma\u00e7\u00e3o de conhecimentos sociais tem seu in\u00edcio na inf\u00e2ncia, a escola de educa\u00e7\u00e3o infantil tem papel fundamental para a promo\u00e7\u00e3o da reflex\u00e3o acerca do consumismo que afeta negativamente as crian\u00e7as. Conhecer a vis\u00e3o dos professores, do ambiente escolar e as cren\u00e7as das crian\u00e7as sobre o consumismo infantil, pode trazer importantes elementos para a reflex\u00e3o de pais, professores, pesquisadores e interessados nessa tem\u00e1tica",
                "The consumer society destroys planetary health, because in addition to increasingly degrading the environment as if there were an inexhaustible source of natural resources, it contributes negatively to the formation of citizens who are unaware of their real needs and already affects the formation of children's identity. since early childhood, as they are provoked by having objects and consuming cultural artifacts without any criticism, overlapping with being. Child consumerism causes various problems in childhood (anxiety, family stress, created needs and repressed desires, obesity, early sexualization, etc.). Considering that the formation of social knowledge begins in childhood, the kindergarten plays a fundamental role in promoting reflection on consumerism that negatively affects children. Knowing the views of teachers, the school environment and children's beliefs about child consumerism can provide important elements for reflection by parents, teachers, researchers and those interested in this topic"
            ],
